Critical Next.js 16 Changes from v15

params, searchParams, cookies(), headers(), draftMode() are ALL async — synchronous access is fully removed (no fallback)
Turbopack is default — no --turbopack flag needed. Custom webpack configs fail builds unless --webpack flag used
turbopack config is top-level (not experimental.turbopack)
middleware.ts → proxy.ts rename (but edge runtime NOT supported in proxy — keep as middleware if using edge)
next lint removed — use Biome CLI directly (pnpm exec biome check .)
experimental_ppr route segment config removed — use cacheComponents: true instead
React Compiler stable — reactCompiler: true (not experimental)
cacheLife and cacheTag stable — no unstable_ prefix
unstable_rootParams removed
serverRuntimeConfig / publicRuntimeConfig removed — use env vars via @t3-oss/env-nextjs
next/legacy/image deprecated
images.domains deprecated → use images.remotePatterns
images.minimumCacheTTL default: 60s → 14400s (4h)
images.qualities default: all → [75] only
Parallel routes: ALL @slot dirs MUST have default.tsx
sitemap id parameter from generateSitemaps is now Promise<string>
Tailwind v4: CSS-first config (@import "tailwindcss" in CSS), NO tailwind.config.js


§ ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
ALL environment variables MUST be accessed through lib/env.ts using @t3-oss/env-nextjs.
NEVER use raw process.env.X anywhere except inside lib/env.ts.

Database — multi-environment
DATABASE_URL=                     # Current environment Neon connection string
DATABASE_URL_DEV=                 # Dev branch (full access)
DATABASE_URL_PREVIEW=             # Preview/staging branch (read + migrate)
DATABASE_URL_PRODUCTION=          # Production (read-only for agent, app has write)
PRISMA_MCP_READONLY=              # "true" in production, "false" in dev
// ✅ Correct
import { env } from '@/lib/env'
const url = env.DATABASE_URL

// ❌ Forbidden
const url = process.env.DATABASE_URL
If a new env var is needed: add to lib/env.ts schema first, then use.

