§ DATABASE WORKFLOW

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    NEON PostgreSQL                    │
│                 (Single source of truth)              │
└──────────┬──────────────────────┬────────────────────┘
           │                      │
    ┌──────▼──────┐       ┌──────▼──────┐
    │ Drizzle ORM │       │ Prisma MCP  │
    │  (App Code) │       │ (AI Agent)  │
    │             │       │             │
    │ • Queries   │       │ • Introspect│
    │ • Relations │       │ • Safe SQL  │
    │ • Types     │       │ • Guardrails│
    │ • Migrations│       │ • Prototype │
    └─────────────┘       └─────────────┘

When to use what:

| Task | Tool | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Write application queries | Drizzle ORM | Type-safe, edge-ready, app code |
| Define/modify schema | Drizzle schema files (`src/db/schema/`) | Single source of truth for app |
| Push schema to DB | `drizzle-kit push` or `drizzle-kit generate` + `migrate` | Drizzle manages migrations |
| Introspect current DB state | Prisma MCP `introspect` | Verify schema drift, validate state |
| Prototype a complex query | Prisma MCP `execute SQL` | Safe sandbox with guardrails |
| Debug production data issue | Prisma MCP `read-only query` | Guardrails prevent accidental writes |
| Create new table (prototyping) | Prisma MCP SQL → then codify in Drizzle schema | Fast iteration → proper code |
| Validate migration safety | Prisma MCP introspect BEFORE and AFTER | Diff check |

FORBIDDEN combinations:
- ❌ NEVER use Prisma MCP to run migrations — Drizzle Kit only
- ❌ NEVER generate Prisma schema files — no schema.prisma
- ❌ NEVER install @prisma/client — MCP runs via npx independently
- ❌ NEVER write app queries through Prisma MCP — Drizzle ORM only

Prototyping → Production workflow:
Step 1: Agent uses Prisma MCP to explore DB / prototype SQL
Step 2: Agent validates query works and returns expected data
Step 3: Agent translates SQL to Drizzle ORM query in app code
Step 4: Agent runs drizzle-kit push if schema changes needed
Step 5: Agent uses Prisma MCP introspect to verify DB matches Drizzle schema
Step 6: Done — Prisma MCP was scaffolding, Drizzle is production code

