Async Request APIs (v16 — non-negotiable)
Every access to these APIs MUST be awaited. Synchronous access is fully removed in v16:
const { slug } = await params;           // page.tsx, layout.tsx, route.tsx
const { q } = await searchParams;        // page.tsx
const cookieStore = await cookies();      // anywhere server-side
const headerList = await headers();       // anywhere server-side
const draft = await draftMode();          // anywhere server-side
const resolvedId = await id;             // sitemap with generateSitemaps
If you write const { slug } = params without await → runtime error in v16.
UI Consistency + Scalable Architecture
Before ANY UI change: SEARCH similar patterns (Filesystem) → AUDIT registry (.agent/registry/components.md) → DECIDE abstraction level → EXTRACT tokens → MATCH same element = same treatment → IMPLEMENT at highest viable level → VERIFY via browser-tools-mcp
Decision hierarchy:

Theme-level (CSS variables, @theme in Tailwind v4 globals.css) → colors, spacing, typography
Component-level (shared components in src/components/ui/) → multi-page patterns
Utility composition → page-specific combinations
Inline → ONLY unique one-off with [DECISION]

